A colloquial Chinese term for "martial arts", literally "to break" (ç ´). Refers to "Focused (spiritual) Animal Hand" styles. The animal force (lung chiku) arts as well as the common hand. Used as an independent word as well as a suffix; [[Maenpo]], IeHsingPo, [[PoKwa Zen]], to do "po".